助教資訊 Contact with Tutor


學習規範 Course Policy
	    § Attendance & Participation: Your attendance, punctuality and participation will all be recorded for evaluation.  2 additional points to the course grade will be rewarded to those who never miss a class, and one absence will be excused.  On the other hand, grade will be deducted for the second and each subsequent absence or lateness: 1 point off every hour of unexcused absence; 0.5 point off any lateness.  Students with 3 absences following the initial one should simply quit the class—exceptional cases must be brought to the attention of the instructor immediately.  In case of unavoidable absence, official document for leave should be forwarded to both the instructor and the administrators in charge.  (See university policy on taking an official leave) 

§ Assignments: All written works should follow standard MLA style format.  Unless otherwise instructed, both print-out and electronic copies are required for submission.  Deadlines should be strictly observed based on online submission.  Penalty applies (3-point deduction per day) for any late work without the instructor’s prior consent.  Work handed in more than a week late will not be accepted.

§ Cell Phone: Turn off or to the vibration mode.  Absolutely no talking on phone in class is allowed.

§ Academic Integrity: Plagiarism/Cheating will not be tolerated.  Please use your discretion lest any violation to academic integrity should occur, albeit unintentionally.
       

