備註 Remarks





基本素養 Basic Literacy
■ 厚植人文素養及西洋文學、語言、文化及知識
 To cultivate their spirit of humanity and increase their knowledge of western literature, languages and cultures.
□ 培養獨立思考、團隊合作及思辨能力、發展關懷與服務精神
 To improve their capabilities for independent thinking, teamwork, and critical analysis and develop their civil concern and spirit of service
□ 擴展國際視野、接受多元文化及跨領域學習
 To broaden their global vision and accept diverse cultures and interdisciplinary 
learning.
 

核心能力 Competence
□ 具備人文素養及社會關懷與服務的能力
 Ability to provide social concern and service with a spirit of humanity.
□ 具備語言學、語言教學理論、知識與應用能力
 Ability to apply professionally the knowledge and theory of linguistics and language teaching.
□ 英外語溝通及應用能力
 Ability to demonstrate foreign language proficiency in various applications.
■ 多面向深入閱讀、賞析外國文學、語言、文化與藝術的能力
 Ability to appreciate and analyze foreign literatures, languages and cultures from multi-dimensional perspectives.
□ 適應多元文化與職場領域的知能
 Abiltiy to accomodate diverse cultures and professional fields.
■ 培養獨立及批判性思考、提問及解決問題的能力
 Ability to think independently and critically and to raise questions and solve problems.
 

課程概述 Course Description
       本課程主要介紹維多利亞時期至20世紀早期之英國作家。課程將著重於作品細讀並進行分析討論，學生應配合預習每週閱讀作業。
This course introduces the major works of British writers between the Victorian period and the early 20th century. Our primary goal, simply put, is to (try to) understand and enjoy the literary texts themselves.  At the same time, it is hoped that as the course progresses, you will develop the ability to recognize the historical, cultural, social and intellectual contexts that contribute to your knowledge of the literary texts, as well as to think critically and independently about these works and their time.  We hope the increasing understanding of the life and thought then and there will help foster diverse perspectives as we live in our own time and place.
Class meetings will focus on close reading analysis and discussion.  In order to facilitate this process, you must keep up with the weekly reading assignments. (Quizzes will be given whenever you seem to fall behind the reading schedule.)  You are encouraged to read each literary work at least twice before class: the first time for its content, and the second time for further observations of specific literary techniques and conventions.  Taking an active part in class and on-line discussion will also help you cultivate your literary sensitivity and exercise your interpretive skills.  Finally, I strongly recommend that you keep a reading journal to help you prepare for class discussion, writing essays, taking exams, etc. (Sample journal entry will be posted on the course website). 
There will be a comprehensive final exam.  It consists of factual questions (true/false, multiple-choice, source identification, etc.), passage analyses and essay question(s). The exam focuses on both your knowledge of the factual aspects of the literary texts and your understanding of their themes.    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    This course introduces the major works of British writers between the Victorian period and the early 20th century. Our primary goal, simply put, is to (try to) understand and enjoy the literary texts themselves.  At the same time, it is hoped that as the course progresses, you will develop the ability to recognize the historical, cultural, social and intellectual contexts that contribute to your knowledge of the literary texts, as well as to think critically and independently about these works and their time.  We hope the increasing understanding of the life and thought then and there will help foster diverse perspectives as we live in our own time and place.
Class meetings will focus on close reading analysis and discussion.  In order to facilitate this process, you must keep up with the weekly reading assignments. (Quizzes will be given whenever you seem to fall behind the reading schedule.)  You are encouraged to read each literary work at least twice before class: the first time for its content, and the second time for further observations of specific literary techniques and conventions.  Taking an active part in class and on-line discussion will also help you cultivate your literary sensitivity and exercise your interpretive skills.  Finally, I strongly recommend that you keep a reading journal to help you prepare for class discussion, writing essays, taking exams, etc. (Sample journal entry will be posted on the course website). 
There will be a comprehensive final exam.  It consists of factual questions (true/false, multiple-choice, source identification, etc.), passage analyses and essay question(s). The exam focuses on both your knowledge of the factual aspects of the literary texts and your understanding of their themes.    

